To map numeric enums to strings, implement a translation function returning a 'const char*'. Here is a robust approach:

```c
#include <stdio.h>
typedef enum { DEV_OFFLINE, DEV_ONLINE, DEV_MAINTENANCE } DeviceState;

const char* get_device_state_string(DeviceState state) {
    switch(state) {
        case DEV_OFFLINE:     return "Offline";
        case DEV_ONLINE:      return "Online";
        case DEV_MAINTENANCE: return "Maintenance";
        default:              return "Unknown State";
    }
}
```

